RESOURCE.STRING: Actuator Diagnostic Tests
These actuator diagnostic tests can be used to diagnose failed throttle actuators, compressor by-pass actuators, or fuel control valve actuators.

Initial Conditions
1. Key On
2. Engine stopped
3. Troubleshoot all fault codes before starting the test

Steps
1. Select the actuators that are to be tested
2. Select Automatic or Manual Test
3. If Manual Test is selected the desired position will need to be entered manually in steps of 1 percent.
4. If Automatic test is selected INSITE will move the actuator back and forth in 20 percent steps.
5. Select Start
6. Select Stop to stop the test or to make changes to the test setup.
This test is not supported by the current calibration.
